This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it proposes a new model predictive control formulation for autonomous driving. It also considers the non-linear actuator dynamics of the vehicle, which is a common topic in robotics. The System and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with control theory and optimization. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to optimize the control inputs, which makes the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category a possibility. The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with decision-making algorithms for autonomous driving. Finally, the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category is a possibility as the paper may use visual data to make decisions about the vehicle's trajectory.
